From: elizaOS chip team <chip-team@elizaos.invalid>
Subject: [PATCH] cva6: bht.sv work around V3Delayed whole-array NBA limitation

Same root cause as btb-v3delayed-workaround.patch: the simulator's
C++ lowering pass cannot handle a whole-array non-blocking assignment
to a 2D unpacked struct array

    bht_q[NR_ROWS-1:0][CVA6Cfg.INSTR_PER_FETCH-1:0]

and aborts with

    Internal Error: ../V3Delayed.cpp:958: Unexpected LHS form

at core/frontend/bht.sv:122 -- `bht_q <= bht_d;`.

This patch replaces the whole-array NBA with an explicit per-element
nested for-loop.  The two forms are semantically equivalent but the
per-element form exercises the supported per-element NBA lowering path.

Tracked alongside the btb workaround in
external/cva6/pin-manifest.json::verilator_full_conversion_blocker.
The patch is applied by scripts/apply_cva6_patches.sh before each
simulator run.
---
 core/frontend/bht.sv | 13 ++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/core/frontend/bht.sv b/core/frontend/bht.sv
index e95c536..a1f8a85 100644
--- a/core/frontend/bht.sv
+++ b/core/frontend/bht.sv
@@ -119,7 +119,18 @@ module bht #(
             end
           end
         end else begin
-          bht_q <= bht_d;
+          // Local workaround for an internal-error in the C++ lowering
+          // pass on whole-array NBA to a 2D unpacked struct array
+          // (see V3Delayed.cpp:958 Unexpected LHS form).  The
+          // per-element nested loop below is semantically equivalent
+          // and exercises the supported per-element NBA path.  See
+          // patches/cva6/bht-v3delayed-workaround.patch in the
+          // consuming repo.
+          for (int i = 0; i < NR_ROWS; i++) begin
+            for (int j = 0; j < CVA6Cfg.INSTR_PER_FETCH; j++) begin
+              bht_q[i][j] <= bht_d[i][j];
+            end
+          end
         end
       end
     end
